= configuring vim =
Creating a vimrc is the first step  [[topic/vimrc]].
Writing ftplugin/*.vim files is the next (configure vim for some filetypes only).

If you need more control you can try auto commands like this:

{{{
augroup YOUR_PROJECT
  autocmd BufRead,BufNewFile PATH_TO_YOUR_PROJECT/**/*.c	set sw=2
augroup end
}}}

or use local-vimrc plugins such as [[http://github.com/MarcWeber/vim-addon-local-vimrc|vim-addon-local-vimrc]]

Also modeline can be used (the :vim line you'll find at every :help page) which looks like this:
{{{
vim:tw=78:fo=tcq2:isk=!-~,^*,^\|,^\":ts=8:ft=help:norl:
}}}
